Charles William Ingram (born 6 August 1963) is an English criminal and former British Army major who made headlines worldwide after cheating to win the one million pounds jackpot on the game show Who Wants To Be A Millionaire? in 2001. He was subsequently convicted at Southwark Crown Court on a single count of deception. An unrelated conviction, for insurance fraud, followed in 2003.
He is married to Diana Ingram (born 1965) and has since participated in other television shows, including Weakest Link (where he appeared with his wife Diana, lasting until the sixth round), Wife Swap (in which he swapped lives with Jade Goody's boyfriend) and Hell's Kitchen and controversially on Big Brother's Big Mouth.
